HEADWORD: Smicker
<hw>Smick"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Akin to Sw.
<ets>smickra</ets> to flatter, Dan. <ets>smigre</ets>, and perhaps to G.
<ets>schmeicheln</ets>, and E. <ets>smile</ets>. Cf. <er>Smicker</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To look amorously or wantonly; to
smirk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

